--8<-- [start:description]

Ensures that `~/.pixi/bin` (or `$PIXI_HOME/bin`) is on your shell's `PATH`.
Automatically detects your shell and appends the appropriate snippet to the
right config file.

Supported shells: `bash`, `zsh`, `fish`, `nushell`, `powershell`, `xonsh`.

--8<-- [end:description]
--8<-- [start:example]

## Examples

Auto-detect your shell and update its config file:
```shell
pixi global shell-init
```

Target a specific shell:
```shell
pixi global shell-init --shell fish
```

Only print the snippet (do not modify any files):
```shell
pixi global shell-init --print
pixi global shell-init --shell nushell --print
```

Overwrite a previously configured snippet (e.g. after changing `$PIXI_HOME`):
```shell
pixi global shell-init --force
```

--8<-- [end:example]
